\title{direct image}
\date{2024-01-31}
\author{jonmsterling}
\contributor{marcelofiore}
\taxon{definition}
\import{jms-00JB}

\p{Let #{R\colon A\relto B} be a [relation](jms-00I7). The \dem{direct image} of #{X\subseteq A} under #{R} is the set #{\dir-img{R}{X}\subseteq B} defined below:}

##{
 \dir-img{R}{X} =
 \compr{b\in B}{\exists x\in X\punctdot x\mathrel{R}b}
}